===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|人|alt1=亻|t1=person|壬|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p}} – to carry on a shoulder pole.

Note that its phonetic part {{och-l|壬|id=2}} may be the graphical representation of {{lang|zh|任}}, depicting a shoulder pole rotated by 90 degrees.

===Etymology===
Cognate with {{och-l|妊|pregnant}} and {{cog|bo|སྣོམ་པ||to take; seize; hold}}. May also be cognate with {{cog|qfa-kms-pro|*ȵam¹||to hold}} and {{cog|okz|nāṃ||to carry}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Note also similarities with {{cog|my|နှံ|t=to entrust}} ({{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}}).

